NASHVILLE — The best show in town Saturday night wrapped up with a Lightning victory over the Predators in Tampa Bay’s first outdoor game. A few notable numbers from the Stadium Series at the Tennessee Titans’ Nissan Stadium: 1 Game won by Tampa Bay teams at Nissan Stadium. The Bucs are 0-4 against the Titans here. 10 Minutes Miranda Lambert and Dierks Bentley spent performing five songs during the first intermission concert. 15 Artists performing in the Stadium Series including Lambert (first intermission), Bentley (first intermission), Jessie James Decker (U.S. national anthem), Dustin Lynch (introduction), Walker Hayes (pre-game TikTok). 40.3 Temperature at puck drop Saturday night. 51 Amount, in dollars, for a Stadium Series-themed harmonica sold in the Nissan Stadium gift shops. 85 Approximate steps it took Lightning captain Steven Stamkos to get from the gate along the ice to the tunnel entrance. 243 Ice pans under the rink at Nissan Stadium to hold water to build the ice surface. 350 Gallons of paint used to make the ice at Nissan Stadium white. This year, the league started building the ice sooner and painted the logos deeper into the ice with the expectation of rain in the days leading up to the game. 890 Games before Stamkos played in an NHL outdoor series, the second-longest stretch among active players behind center Joe Thornton, who competed in his first (2015′s Stadium Series) after previously playing in 1,263 games. 68,619 Fans in attendance Saturday, the largest crowd the Lightning have played in front of. • • • The Tampa Bay Times has commemorated the Lightning’s second consecutive Stanley Cup title with a new hardcover coffee table book, Striking Twice. Order now. Sign up for Lightning Strikes, a weekly newsletter from Bolts beat writer Eduardo A. Encina that brings you closer to the ice. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.